The Bible says that he inhabits the praises of his people.

01:27.256 --> 01:30.000
I think that means he's here with us today.

01:30.060 --> 01:35.186
And you made it to church on the Sunday before Christmas.

01:37.890 --> 01:44.066
Whether you're at one of our locations or you're joining us online, I know that that means that your heart is expectant today.

01:44.106 --> 01:48.959
That you want more than just checking off things off your to-do list this week.

01:48.979 --> 01:50.322
That you want to get your heart right.

01:50.658 --> 01:59.848
this week, and you wanna be in the presence of Jesus, and I believe that God has a word for us today, and I'm really honored that I get to bring it to you.

02:00.068 --> 02:04.974
So, okay, real quick, before you take your seats, I just wanna read our scripture for today.

02:05.014 --> 02:08.658
I'm gonna be reading from Luke chapter one, if you have a Bible.

02:09.939 --> 02:18.428
And last week, Pastor Stephen talked about how God provides, and he prompts.

02:18.668 --> 02:20.210
It was so powerful, were you here?

02:21.634 --> 02:22.315
Amazing.

02:23.016 --> 02:24.817
This sermon was called Mary's Prayer.

02:24.858 --> 02:30.283
And so I want to pick up today with a little bit more of Mary's story.

02:30.303 --> 02:32.486
And we're going to start reading in the middle of the passage.

02:32.786 --> 02:38.793
The angel has come to Mary and he's announced to her that she's going to give birth to the Son of God.

02:39.093 --> 02:41.456
And we're going to start reading right there in verse 34.

02:41.716 --> 02:44.659
Mary asked the angel, but how can this happen?

02:45.300 --> 02:46.021
I am a virgin.

02:46.041 --> 02:51.026
And the angel replied, the Holy Spirit will come upon you.

02:51.362 --> 02:54.905
and the power of the most high will overshadow you.

02:55.466 --> 03:00.731
So the baby to be born will be holy, and he will be called the son of God."

03:00.791 --> 03:04.494
What's more, your relative Elizabeth has become pregnant in her old age.

03:04.915 --> 03:13.303
People used to say she was barren, but she has conceived a son and is now in her sixth month for no word from God will ever fail.

03:15.505 --> 03:18.408
Mary replied, I am the Lord's servant.

03:19.028 --> 03:21.010
May everything that you have said about me

03:21.346 --> 03:21.887
come true.

03:22.489 --> 03:24.654
And then the angel left her.

03:25.817 --> 03:31.091
A few days later, Mary hurried to the hill country of Judea to the town where Zechariah lived.

03:31.512 --> 03:33.597
She entered the house and greeted Elizabeth.

03:34.038 --> 03:37.106
At the sound of Mary's greeting, Elizabeth's child leaped

03:37.250 --> 03:40.795
within her and Elizabeth was filled with the Holy Spirit.

03:41.115 --> 03:48.045
Elizabeth gave a glad cry and exclaimed to Mary, God has blessed you above all women and your child is blessed.

03:48.065 --> 03:51.790
Why am I so honored that the mother of my Lord should visit me?

03:51.830 --> 03:55.996
When I heard your greeting, the baby in my womb jumped for joy.

03:56.036 --> 04:03.506
You are blessed because you believed that the Lord would do what he said.

04:04.994 --> 04:07.379
Father, would you bless the reading of this word today?

04:07.399 --> 04:09.583
We love you, we want to hear from you.

04:09.643 --> 04:11.828
It's in Jesus' name we pray, amen.

04:11.928 --> 04:14.693
All right, the title of my sermon, don't sit down yet, don't sit down yet.

04:16.116 --> 04:20.866
The title of my sermon is blessed because you believed.

04:22.128 --> 04:24.914
On your way to your seat, ask your neighbor, are you blessed?

04:34.114 --> 04:44.044
So several weeks ago, my husband stood up here and he told all of you about how I am a terrible liar.

04:45.906 --> 04:46.467
It's true.

04:46.747 --> 04:51.552
I don't know why, but I am really just the worst liar.

04:51.572 --> 04:57.278
And what that means is don't ask me if I like your haircut.

04:58.519 --> 05:01.522
Please do not put me on the spot like that because sometimes

05:02.178 --> 05:11.589
I just can't think of anything to say and like the best thing that I might be able to come up with is like, wow, you look so good.

05:11.749 --> 05:12.911
And then you won't believe me.

05:13.051 --> 05:15.554
And I'm, you know, I just, I'm a terrible liar.

05:15.774 --> 05:23.223
And what that means though also is that my inability to lie, it also makes me extremely gullible.

05:23.984 --> 05:25.526
I, I'm just, I'm a believer.

05:25.826 --> 05:26.126
Okay.

05:26.186 --> 05:29.330
So I am a car salesman's dream.

05:29.442 --> 05:33.488
You know, like I'm going to be like, yeah, like a little old lady drove this car.

05:33.528 --> 05:35.932
She only drove it to church in the grocery store every week.

05:35.972 --> 05:38.636
I mean, I just, I just believe what people say to me.

05:38.676 --> 05:45.486
And I also believe I've recently come to realize everything that comes into my Instagram feed.

05:46.147 --> 05:49.773
And this drives my family crazy.

05:50.174 --> 05:54.500
Like I will frequently show my kids videos and be like, look at this.

05:54.540 --> 05:55.722
This is amazing.

05:55.762 --> 05:58.386
And my kids will look back at me and they're like, mom,

05:58.530 --> 05:59.391
That's not real.

06:00.894 --> 06:02.457
And so then I'll find another one.

06:02.477 --> 06:05.962
I want to show, I got to show Steven so I'll say, you're not going to believe this.

06:06.022 --> 06:08.987
And he'll look at me and he'll be like, Holly, you know, that's AI, right?

06:09.829 --> 06:10.129
Okay.

06:10.149 --> 06:10.991
So I'm slow.

06:11.091 --> 06:13.936
I'm learning because I just believe that things are true.

06:13.976 --> 06:18.082
Like the other day, this video came into my feed on Instagram.

06:18.283 --> 06:22.370
And I don't know if you guys saw this one, but it was ring doorbell footage.

06:23.151 --> 06:25.074
And which means it's true.

06:25.538 --> 06:31.227
And there was a cat and a baby on a front porch.

06:31.807 --> 06:34.231
And a bear wanders up.

06:34.251 --> 06:39.539
And the cat hisses and like swats at the bear and saves the baby.

06:40.521 --> 06:47.031
And when I saw this video, I thought, wow, that is one amazing cat.

06:48.993 --> 06:54.642
And a couple days later, another one comes into my feet, different porch, different cat.

06:54.850 --> 06:58.855
Different baby and I thought, I think we need to get a cat.

07:01.618 --> 07:03.681
So then a third one came.

07:04.602 --> 07:08.127
And this time, I thought, wait a minute.

07:08.908 --> 07:12.893
Like, how many moms are leaving their babies alone on a porch?

07:14.074 --> 07:15.336
This must be a eye.

07:15.376 --> 07:17.298
You can't fool me three times.

07:17.826 --> 07:23.272
I recently saw another one of this family of dolphins and they were like breaching the water.

07:23.913 --> 07:28.317
And this tiny little baby dolphin like pops up out of the water.

07:28.377 --> 07:31.320
It was the cutest thing I have seen in 2025.

07:31.861 --> 07:34.123
And I was like, oh, wait, maybe this.

07:34.524 --> 07:38.728
So I went to the comments because, you know, in the comments, people will let you know if this is AI.

07:39.389 --> 07:43.954
And one of the first comments that I saw this woman said, if this is AI, don't tell me.

07:44.738 --> 07:45.699
I don't want to know.

07:45.759 --> 07:47.821
And I was like, amen, it's real.

07:48.842 --> 07:52.246
How many of you would agree it's getting harder and harder to believe?

07:53.647 --> 07:56.831
When I was in my 20s, I felt that belief was black and white.

07:57.271 --> 07:58.252
This is what I believe.

07:58.693 --> 08:00.094
This is what I do not believe.

08:00.595 --> 08:02.757
And I believe that this is what you should believe too.

08:02.917 --> 08:04.359
I was really fun to be around.

08:04.379 --> 08:05.260
You would have enjoyed it.

08:05.740 --> 08:11.186
As I've gotten older though, I've learned to let go kind of of the black and white.

08:11.490 --> 08:21.400
And I've had to learn that believing God is so much more about who He is than it is about what I think He should do.

08:21.460 --> 08:29.208
And in our story, Elizabeth told Mary that she was blessed because she believed.

08:29.949 --> 08:33.813
And when I read this, those words just leapt off of the page for me.

08:33.853 --> 08:38.738
The blessings in my life are directly tied to my beliefs.

08:39.010 --> 08:46.621
What I believe about God has to be at the center of everything that I say and everything that I do.

08:46.661 --> 08:51.388
And what I want you to know today is that God is not Santa.

08:52.690 --> 08:55.233
We don't grow out of believing in Him.

08:55.293 --> 09:01.362
We grow into our belief as we walk with Him.

09:01.954 --> 09:04.277
as we begin our journey with Him.

09:04.317 --> 09:06.461
We begin it with salvation, right?

09:06.481 --> 09:10.226
Maybe you accepted Jesus as a child and you've known Him your whole life.

09:10.246 --> 09:15.614
Maybe you accepted Jesus here at Elevation, you raised your hand and you got one of those orange Bibles.

09:15.634 --> 09:18.378
Maybe you accepted Jesus online through our ministry.

09:18.418 --> 09:22.263
We begin by knowing Jesus as our Savior.

09:22.624 --> 09:27.131
But then we get to know that God is so much more than that.

09:27.471 --> 09:29.554
God never intended for us to stop.

09:29.698 --> 09:30.500
with salvation.

09:30.560 --> 09:34.668
The gospel is not about accepting Jesus just so that we can go to heaven.

09:34.728 --> 09:36.732
That's the beginning and the end.

09:37.113 --> 09:40.159
But you will be blessed because you believed in Him.

09:40.459 --> 09:49.778
The gospel is about believing in God and getting to know Him in the middle part, in the time that we have here on earth.

09:50.274 --> 10:03.154
we get to know God when we worship Him, when we bring our questions to Him and our sorrows and our disappointments, and when we lay them before Him, and we begin to grow in our belief of who He is.

10:04.496 --> 10:09.564
This February, our church is gonna celebrate our 20th anniversary.

10:10.285 --> 10:14.751
And I'm so excited, I just want you to know, we're going big.

10:15.593 --> 10:19.058
I've told my husband, I was like, we're doing this right.

10:19.362 --> 10:20.964
20 years is a big deal.

10:20.984 --> 10:24.870
So I've been combing through old videos and pictures.

10:24.970 --> 10:30.458
And I've just been feeling all of the feelings of what it's been like these past 20 years.

10:30.539 --> 10:45.260
And I just want to tell you, it has been the blessing of a lifetime to believe that God could use two kids from South Carolina to be able to lead a church and a ministry like this.

10:45.681 --> 10:49.106
We were 25 years old when we started this church.

10:49.922 --> 10:56.276
I don't know who wanted to come to a church led by two 25 year old kids, but thank you for coming.

10:56.777 --> 11:01.628
And I'm so glad that God did actually call us to start this when we were young.

11:02.170 --> 11:05.938
When we started this church, I was so naive.

11:06.082 --> 11:11.468
And Stephen tells this story, I'm sure you've heard about how we were on our front porch in Shelby, North Carolina.

11:11.769 --> 11:15.753
And I looked at him and I said, it's time for us to start this church.

11:15.994 --> 11:24.043
And I believed with all of my heart that God was calling us to go and to do this and to step out in faith and to follow him.

11:24.263 --> 11:33.554
But I had no idea how much I would grow in my understanding of who he is as we walked out

11:33.698 --> 11:37.021
what we believed that he was calling us to do.

11:37.041 --> 11:41.585
I want you to know that I have come to know God as Jehovah Jairah.

11:42.406 --> 11:57.260
Because from the moment that we took the first step to move to Charlotte, we've seen him provide over and over and over again, every person that he put in our path, every resource that he prompted someone to give, every connection that led us to the next step.

11:57.481 --> 12:03.186
I've also come to know him as Jehovah Nissi, the one who fights our battles,

12:03.330 --> 12:03.951
for us.

12:04.632 --> 12:07.977
I've come to know him as Jehovah Raffa, the God who heals.

12:08.057 --> 12:17.250
And I've seen him bring healing and restoration to so many people across our ministries, families that were put back together, marriages that were restored.

12:17.510 --> 12:25.101
I've come to know him as Emmanuel, God with us in the ups and the downs and in everything in between.

12:25.441 --> 12:28.966
I have come to know that God is with me.

12:29.307 --> 12:31.570
I am blessed because I

12:31.682 --> 12:35.146
believed and you are blessed because you believe.

12:35.807 --> 12:46.540
And the Christmas story is about a cast of characters who dared to believe that God was telling them what would come to pass and that it was true.

12:47.842 --> 12:50.345
So my message today is very simple.

12:50.505 --> 12:55.511
It's so simple that I'm almost embarrassed that this is what I'm bringing to you.

12:55.571 --> 12:57.553
It's very common sense.

12:57.673 --> 13:01.458
And in the time that we have left, I want to show you three things.

13:01.602 --> 13:06.449
that I believe about God that I see in this part of the Christmas story.

13:06.470 --> 13:12.599
And I just wanna warn you my parts, my points, they're not catchy, they don't rhyme, they don't spell anything at the end.

13:12.639 --> 13:16.585
So don't be prepared to be in awe at the end.

13:16.605 --> 13:19.329
We're gonna leave that for when Pastor Stephen comes back.

13:20.231 --> 13:21.813
It's just a simple message today.

13:21.853 --> 13:26.841
Three truths that we can believe about God this Christmas.

13:27.502 --> 13:30.066
And the first one is, I believe

13:30.722 --> 13:32.824
that God believes in me.

13:34.165 --> 13:36.768
Let's go back to our scripture, verse 26.

13:36.848 --> 13:44.735
In the sixth month of Elizabeth's pregnancy, God sent the angel Gabriel to Nazareth, a village in Galilee, to a virgin named Mary.

13:45.236 --> 13:48.839
She was engaged to be married to a man named Joseph, a descendant of King David.

13:49.460 --> 13:54.705
Gabriel appeared to her and said, Greetings, favored woman, the Lord is with you.

13:55.306 --> 13:59.890
Confused and disturbed, Mary tried to think what the angel could mean.

14:00.354 --> 14:06.183
Don't be afraid, the angel told her, for you have found favor with God.

14:07.485 --> 14:16.119
Now, nowhere in this passage do we find a reason why God picked Mary.

14:16.961 --> 14:19.445
God didn't pick Mary because she was strong.

14:19.845 --> 14:20.586
It doesn't say that.

14:21.027 --> 14:23.591
God didn't pick Mary because she was accomplished.

14:23.872 --> 14:24.693
It doesn't say that.

14:25.074 --> 14:27.858
God didn't pick Mary because she was experienced.

14:27.938 --> 14:29.861
She did not apply for this job.

14:30.201 --> 14:32.064
She did not campaign for this job.

14:32.364 --> 14:34.327
And she did not volunteer for this job.

14:34.607 --> 14:40.495
But one day, an angel comes to her and he says, you have found favor with God.

14:41.696 --> 14:52.431
Now, when I think of the mother that I would have picked for Jesus, if I was God, I would have picked a woman that already had a full brood of children.

14:53.011 --> 14:57.938
A woman whose children were homeschooled and responsible

14:58.114 --> 15:13.416
Like, they had a short chart that they actually used, and a woman whose children were respectful, a woman whose children looked after each other, and I would have picked a woman who knew the difference between Croupe and pneumonia.

15:13.897 --> 15:23.370
I would have picked a woman whose house was clean and orderly, and especially I would have picked a woman who could cook good, home-cooked meals for the Son of God.

15:24.812 --> 15:25.874
But God picked Mary.

15:26.690 --> 15:34.904
And all we know about Mary is that she was a virgin who was blessed because she believed that she was the one for the job.

15:35.425 --> 15:37.629
And that's all that God requires of you as well.

15:38.771 --> 15:47.325
And I wonder how different my day would be if I woke up each morning and I said out loud, God picked me for this.

15:49.008 --> 15:50.450
God picked me for this day.

15:50.510 --> 15:52.594
God picked me for this job.

15:52.834 --> 16:06.229
God picked me for this child, whatever the circumstances were that led me to this moment that I am in today, I am going to operate under the belief that God believes I am the one for this.

16:07.590 --> 16:17.982
Now, I think we all live in the tension of the things in our life that we feel called to and the things in our life that we might not necessarily have chosen for ourselves.

16:18.042 --> 16:21.906
Like, there are things in life that we go after.

16:22.018 --> 16:22.278
Right?

16:22.539 --> 16:24.341
God put a desire in your heart.

16:24.361 --> 16:26.063
He gave you a gift and a passion.

16:26.103 --> 16:27.905
And yes, it's hard along the way.

16:27.945 --> 16:31.510
And yes, there are obstacles and things that you have to overcome.

16:31.910 --> 16:35.875
But you're going after what you feel like you are supposed to do.

16:36.175 --> 16:37.497
Anybody ever feel that way?

16:37.757 --> 16:38.758
And it's wonderful.

16:38.999 --> 16:39.740
And you should.

16:39.820 --> 16:43.785
When you feel like you're called to do something, you should go after it.

16:43.845 --> 16:50.012
But then there are things in life that, I don't know, it seems like they go after you.

16:51.033 --> 16:51.474
Right?

16:51.586 --> 17:06.546
Like the things that you didn't plan for, or the things you didn't expect, or the things that you don't feel qualified for, the things that seem to have just been like placed in your life or in your lap that you did not ask for.

17:06.586 --> 17:12.253
And I want you to hear from me that God believes in you.

17:13.094 --> 17:14.115
He chose you.

17:14.176 --> 17:19.122
He chose you to be born at this time, at this place,

17:19.298 --> 17:22.943
In this family, He gave you the children that you have.

17:23.204 --> 17:25.527
He gave you the opportunities that you have.

17:25.827 --> 17:27.309
He chose you.

17:27.690 --> 17:32.036
God believed in you before you believed in Him.

17:32.056 --> 17:37.404
Before the world began, He knew the number of your days.

17:37.865 --> 17:39.166
You are not an accident.

17:39.507 --> 17:44.434
You are chosen and selected to glorify God with your life.

17:44.514 --> 17:47.518
I don't care what you've done or what you have not done.

17:47.558 --> 17:54.006
The only thing that disqualifies you from being used by God is believing the lie that he can't use you.

17:55.388 --> 17:55.769
That's it.

17:57.311 --> 17:58.432
God believes in you.

17:58.452 --> 18:01.236
You're chosen even when you don't feel capable.

18:01.516 --> 18:04.140
You're chosen even when you don't feel like you deserve it.

18:04.440 --> 18:05.341
You're chosen.

18:05.361 --> 18:12.050
And if you wait until you feel ready or worthy or qualified,

18:12.162 --> 18:16.848
or prepared enough, you're gonna miss what God has for you.

18:16.868 --> 18:21.253
You're gonna miss the opportunities that are right in front of you today.

18:21.273 --> 18:26.620
So Mary accepted the calling that God placed on her life.

18:27.361 --> 18:28.583
She said, I am the Lord's servant.

18:29.063 --> 18:31.126
May it be to me as you have said.

18:31.146 --> 18:32.768
It's my favorite verse in the whole Bible.

18:33.128 --> 18:34.810
It's the thing I wanna operate from.

18:34.850 --> 18:36.212
It's the way I wanna live my life.

18:36.272 --> 18:38.215
Okay, God, I'm your servant.

18:38.795 --> 18:40.978
May it be to me as you have said.

18:41.954 --> 18:48.600
And then the scripture tells us that she moved in the direction that she felt that God was leading her.

18:49.101 --> 18:53.425
So the second thing that I believe is I believe that God leads me.

18:54.846 --> 19:04.095
Now, this one is tricky because unfortunately, God does not always spell everything out for us, right?

19:04.576 --> 19:11.122
He doesn't like write our next steps in the sky, but he does strongly suggest

19:11.522 --> 19:12.986
what we should do next.

19:13.387 --> 19:14.209
Look at Mary again.

19:14.269 --> 19:15.031
This is verse 35.

19:15.212 --> 19:22.411
It says, the angel replied, the Holy Spirit will come upon you and the power of the most high will overshadow you.

19:22.471 --> 19:27.203
So the baby to be born will be holy and he will be called the son of God.

19:27.544 --> 19:28.306
What's more?

19:28.834 --> 19:31.857
Your relative Elizabeth has become pregnant in her old age.

19:32.157 --> 19:38.604
People used to say that she was barren, but she has conceived the sun and is now in her sixth month for the word of God will never fail.

19:38.644 --> 19:40.947
And Mary responded, here it is, I'm the Lord's servant.

19:41.367 --> 19:43.750
May everything you said about me come true.

19:44.110 --> 19:45.952
And then the angel left her.

19:47.053 --> 19:52.499
I want you to know that sometimes what's next is what you already know.

19:52.539 --> 19:55.762
The angel left Mary

19:56.706 --> 20:02.252
And I imagine that she had to sort of like take in everything that had just happened.

20:03.994 --> 20:07.938
She was like, okay, did that just happen?

20:07.958 --> 20:08.619
Okay, what happened?

20:09.980 --> 20:11.722
And she's replaying it in her mind.

20:12.323 --> 20:16.087
Okay, the angel came and he said I was gonna give birth to the son of God.

20:18.069 --> 20:20.612
But then he said something about my relative Elizabeth.

20:22.073 --> 20:23.174
Elizabeth is pregnant.

20:23.995 --> 20:26.578
Well, let me go see if that's true.

20:27.938 --> 20:34.126
So verse 39 says a few days later, Mary hurried to the hill country of Judea to the town.

20:36.128 --> 20:37.150
Where's Zechariah lived?

20:37.650 --> 20:40.714
She entered the house and greeted Elizabeth.

20:41.435 --> 20:49.145
Sometimes the next step is the thing that you already know to do, but you haven't done it yet.

20:51.167 --> 20:56.754
The thing is, God's not going to reveal more to you until you do that.

20:59.266 --> 21:03.674
Now one of the ways that God leads us is through the people that he puts on our path.

21:03.694 --> 21:05.738
So God led Mary to Elizabeth.

21:06.199 --> 21:18.782
But when Mary got to Elizabeth home, she enters the house and the moment she opens her mouth to say hello, the baby in Elizabeth's womb jumps and confirms what the angel said.

21:18.822 --> 21:21.106
And Elizabeth says to Mary,

21:21.218 --> 21:24.603
Why am I so honored that the mother of my Lord should visit me?

21:24.704 --> 21:30.373
God will send you people when you move towards what you know."

21:32.937 --> 21:43.954
God led Mary and Joseph to Bethlehem because of the census that was ordered, and it was there that the baby was born in a barn, but it was also there that the shepherds came and visited them and they said,

21:44.002 --> 21:48.250
We saw an entire host of angels and we came to worship the Christ child.

21:48.550 --> 21:51.836
And then eight days after that, they took Jesus to the temple.

21:51.976 --> 21:52.898
It was the custom.

21:52.978 --> 21:54.802
It was the thing that they were supposed to do.

21:55.082 --> 21:58.047
It was what you did with your baby when they were eight days old.

21:58.108 --> 22:00.712
You came to the temple and you dedicated them there.

22:01.113 --> 22:08.306
And when they were there, Mary and Joseph, they ran into two different people, Simeon and Anna, the prophetess.

22:08.482 --> 22:12.990
And at the temple, both Simeon and Anna, confirm what God is doing.

22:13.370 --> 22:16.676
And they said, this is Jesus.

22:16.736 --> 22:20.503
And they proclaimed, we have seen the salvation of the Lord.

22:20.543 --> 22:25.251
The path for Mary was going to be so challenging.

22:25.872 --> 22:26.994
But I believe

22:27.202 --> 22:48.140
that every time that doubt crept into Mary's heart when she thought she didn't have what it took to be a good mom, when she thought she didn't know how she was going to protect her son or how she was supposed to provide for him, I believe that she could recall what God had spoken to her through Elizabeth, through Simeon, through Anna, through the shepherds, through the wise men.

22:48.160 --> 22:51.186
And I want you to know that God is going to guide you too.

22:51.810 --> 22:54.294
He's going to tell you what you need to know.

22:54.334 --> 23:02.346
And as long as you keep moving in what you know, he's going to send people to confirm that you are on the right path.

23:02.366 --> 23:07.534
But it's important to know that God's not going to reveal the entire plan to you.

23:07.574 --> 23:12.322
God is going to show you what you need to see when you need to see it.

23:13.343 --> 23:17.930
The angel came to Mary and said, the Holy Spirit will come upon you.

23:18.691 --> 23:20.434
The angel didn't give her a timeline.

23:20.738 --> 23:22.850
He didn't say, see we know the story.

23:22.890 --> 23:24.761
So it's easier for us, right?

23:25.224 --> 23:26.994
But Daniel didn't say to her, okay.

23:27.554 --> 23:30.236
First you're gonna have the baby and he's gonna be born in Bethlehem.

23:30.276 --> 23:33.319
I know that's weird, but you're gonna be there by accident kind of for the senses.

23:33.679 --> 23:40.966
Then you're gonna go to Egypt for two years because Herod's gonna kill all the baby boys and it's not gonna be safe for Jesus to stay in Judea.

23:41.006 --> 23:43.828
But eventually you're gonna come back and you're gonna settle in Nazareth.

23:43.848 --> 23:46.611
And Jesus' ministry isn't gonna even start until he's 30.

23:46.931 --> 23:48.772
So you'll have him for 30 years with you.

23:49.093 --> 23:51.955
And then you're gonna get to see him do this amazing ministry.

23:51.975 --> 23:55.358
And he's gonna perform these incredible ministry miracles.

23:55.678 --> 23:57.540
And then the things that he's gonna do is

23:57.520 --> 24:01.465
He's going to blow your mind, but then he's going to die on the cross, and it's going to be awful.

24:01.485 --> 24:03.788
But don't worry, because he's going to rise again on the third day.

24:03.808 --> 24:04.589
It's all part of the plan.

24:07.693 --> 24:11.638
And I think as parents, we want that for our kids.

24:12.299 --> 24:14.802
Like, wouldn't it be nice if they came with a timeline?

24:15.503 --> 24:16.364
And we were like, it's okay.

24:16.384 --> 24:17.586
It's all part of the plan.

24:19.074 --> 24:28.895
Here's where they're gonna struggle, here's where they're gonna shine, and this is what you should do when this happens, and this is what you should do when that happens, and you should intervene here, but don't worry here.

24:28.955 --> 24:35.931
God doesn't work like that, because God is more concerned with you than He is about your situation.

24:35.991 --> 24:39.378
God wants a relationship with you.

24:40.898 --> 24:45.084
A couple of weeks ago, Pastor Stephen preached something that I will never forget.

24:45.224 --> 24:55.178
It was just a small point in his sermon, but he did this visual thing that just like, I don't know, it just like reached into my heart and I don't think I'll ever forget it.

24:55.198 --> 24:59.184
But I don't know if you remember this, he said, faith is more like this.

24:59.845 --> 25:04.892
And he kind of like, closes eyes, he put his hands like this out and he said, it's like grappling in the dark.

25:05.433 --> 25:09.298
It's like feeling your way around and trusting God with each

25:09.826 --> 25:11.208
tiny steps that you take.

25:12.009 --> 25:22.082
He said, it's more like this than it is like this, holding tight to what I thought this was going to be.

25:23.103 --> 25:30.092
And then he said, you hold tight to the promise, but you hold loosely to the plan.

25:31.133 --> 25:34.898
Babe, that might have been the most impactful thing that you said this year.

25:35.298 --> 25:36.259
It marked me.

25:36.600 --> 25:42.869
It helped me because how many times in my life have I thought that faith is not wavering.

25:43.290 --> 25:45.393
It's not letting go of the original plan.

25:45.433 --> 25:46.234
I have to believe.

25:46.654 --> 25:54.646
If I just believe, if I just come to him over and over again, reminding him of my plan and eventually everything will happen the way that I thought.

25:54.766 --> 25:58.692
It's so hard to let go of what I thought was the plan.

25:58.712 --> 26:03.058
I don't even want to think about how many times

26:03.138 --> 26:07.825
I have said something to God that was of the nature of, God, this was not the plan.

26:10.129 --> 26:11.431
Maybe you feel that way today.

26:12.693 --> 26:15.157
God, divorce was not in my plan.

26:16.258 --> 26:18.001
Sickness was not in my plan.

26:18.962 --> 26:21.787
Job loss at Christmas time was not in my plan.

26:22.688 --> 26:26.835
And I'm not saying that God causes these hard things to happen to us in life.

26:27.335 --> 26:31.602
What I am saying is that faith is remembering

26:32.258 --> 26:34.520
His name will be called Emmanuel.

26:35.922 --> 26:37.283
God with us.

26:39.306 --> 26:44.652
His plan is to be with me every step of the way.

26:44.692 --> 26:47.515
His plan is to comfort us.

26:47.835 --> 26:51.339
His plan is to guide us through the difficulties.

26:51.559 --> 26:56.424
His plan is to grow us, mature us, and strengthen us in the process.

26:56.725 --> 26:57.906
That's God's plan.

26:58.850 --> 27:06.901
Jeremiah 2911, God says to Jeremiah, I know the plans I have for you, plans to prosper you, not to harm you, plans to give you a hope in the future.

27:06.941 --> 27:22.042
This versus got me through some really hard times because it helps me know that when my plans don't go my way, I hold on to the promise that he has good plans for me.

27:24.405 --> 27:25.627
The plans are his.

27:27.029 --> 27:28.050
The plans are his.

27:28.674 --> 27:29.896
He holds the plans.

27:31.017 --> 27:32.099
We hold on to Him.

27:32.119 --> 27:41.812
The very first promise that was made to Mary was that the Holy Spirit will come upon you.

27:41.852 --> 27:44.996
And you know, you have that promise too.

27:46.478 --> 27:56.031
Jesus told the disciples, this is John 1613, He said, when the Spirit of truth comes, He will guide you into all truth.

27:57.093 --> 27:58.034
The promise

27:58.434 --> 28:01.157
that we cling to is that the Spirit will guide you.

28:02.078 --> 28:04.800
The promise is not a map with turn-by-turn directions.

28:05.701 --> 28:13.169
The promise is that you're taking a journey with the ultimate guide who you know is going to lead you through the hard parts.

28:14.009 --> 28:16.252
Belief is not knowing how God will do it.

28:16.852 --> 28:20.096
Belief is trusting the one who will.

28:20.956 --> 28:23.539
We hold tight to the promise, not to the plan.

28:23.739 --> 28:26.642
I have to tell myself this over and over and over again.

28:26.882 --> 28:28.364
My job is not how.

28:29.406 --> 28:30.527
Man, I want it to be how.

28:30.547 --> 28:31.389
I'm really good at how.

28:32.610 --> 28:33.712
My job is not how.

28:34.593 --> 28:35.515
My job is who?

28:37.377 --> 28:37.998
Who do I trust?

28:39.000 --> 28:43.867
And who is he calling me to be when the plans aren't working out the way that I thought?

28:44.347 --> 28:45.629
I can't control the plan.

28:45.649 --> 28:47.272
I mean, you know what?

28:47.372 --> 28:48.814
I think we all need to say that out loud.

28:49.254 --> 28:49.775
Let's say it together.

28:50.596 --> 28:53.060
I can't control the plan.

28:53.380 --> 28:54.482
But you know what I can't control?

28:57.282 --> 28:57.542
me.

28:57.602 --> 29:00.206
I can control me.

29:01.428 --> 29:04.492
I can control what and who I go to when I feel disappointed.

29:05.714 --> 29:09.499
I can control what I say and what I don't say when I feel frustrated.

29:09.660 --> 29:11.022
I can control my attitude.

29:11.482 --> 29:13.245
I can control most of the time.

29:13.265 --> 29:16.209
I can control my responses when things don't go my way.

29:16.509 --> 29:17.511
I can do that.

29:18.592 --> 29:19.794
That's the faith part.

29:20.546 --> 29:25.492
When things don't go my way, can I release my grip on what I thought would happen?

29:25.752 --> 29:33.281
Can I cling to the one who promised to be with me and do the things that I know he has already told me to do?

29:33.301 --> 29:40.530
You don't get the next step until you do the things that you know he's supposed to do.

29:40.590 --> 29:44.094
So maybe some of you, the word for you today is attitude.

29:45.416 --> 29:47.378
God's like, I just want you to work on your attitude.

29:48.194 --> 29:50.658
In this situation, can you have a better attitude?

29:52.441 --> 29:57.008
Philippians 1, 6 says, he who began a good work and you will be faithful to complete it.

29:57.769 --> 29:59.352
You don't have to know the plan.

30:00.053 --> 30:02.757
You just have to stay close to the one who does.

30:03.959 --> 30:10.610
You have to stay close to the one who promises to be faithful to complete the work that he started.

30:10.850 --> 30:13.713
not the work that I started, the work that he started.

30:13.733 --> 30:20.981
And I know that so many of you came in here this Sunday before Christmas feeling like you don't know what to do next in this situation.

30:21.041 --> 30:26.788
And I want you to know that God is going to show you the next step.

30:27.028 --> 30:28.690
You don't have to solve the puzzle.

30:29.110 --> 30:31.453
You don't have to manipulate the situation.

30:31.793 --> 30:33.976
You don't have to cheat your way into it.

30:34.376 --> 30:36.018
All you have to do is take the hint.

30:36.962 --> 30:41.229
Ask God to open your eyes to see where he is working and ask him.

30:41.269 --> 30:49.963
Ask him to stop asking him to change your situation and start asking him to clearly show you what to do next.

30:50.003 --> 30:51.405
God, spell it out for me.

30:51.766 --> 30:54.330
Make it plain and I will obey.

30:54.390 --> 30:57.435
The point is though, that you're going to him.

30:57.475 --> 31:00.179
You go to him with your problems.

31:00.199 --> 31:04.306
You go to him first and then, like Mary, Mary, Mary,

31:04.514 --> 31:09.722
hurt from the Lord, and then she obeyed, and then God confirmed through Elizabeth.

31:09.963 --> 31:14.069
You go to God, and then he might send a person to encourage you.

31:14.350 --> 31:16.273
He might give you a verse to cling to.

31:16.533 --> 31:18.917
He might give you a song to sing in this season.

31:18.937 --> 31:21.882
He might show you a tiny little next step to take.

31:22.202 --> 31:28.853
If you believe that he leads you, you will be looking for him everywhere you go.

31:30.356 --> 31:31.858
God leads you.

31:33.474 --> 31:37.118
Believe that, do you believe that God will lead you in your situation?

31:37.178 --> 31:47.988
The last thing that I believe is that God hears me.

31:49.910 --> 31:51.532
Oh, this is a hard one to accept.

31:53.073 --> 31:58.478
I think when most people read the Christmas story, they start where we started with the angel coming to Mary.

32:00.160 --> 32:02.322
But God, in the book of Luke,

32:02.850 --> 32:09.898
He begins the Christmas story through Elizabeth Mary's relative and her husband, Zechariah.

32:09.918 --> 32:12.281
I don't know if you've ever read the first chapter of Luke.

32:12.641 --> 32:13.482
It's really beautiful.

32:13.542 --> 32:17.267
It tells like this really beautiful story that God is weaving.

32:17.347 --> 32:25.876
And so in the beginning of Luke, we find Zechariah, he was a priest and his wife Elizabeth was Mary's relative and she was barren.

32:26.637 --> 32:27.578
They had no children.

32:27.598 --> 32:30.802
In a culture where having children

32:31.106 --> 32:34.832
was actually like a mark of how blessed you were.

32:35.333 --> 32:36.374
It was everything.

32:37.155 --> 32:42.464
And Zechariah and Elizabeth had prayed for a child, but God had not answered them.

32:42.884 --> 32:46.630
Look at what Luke tells us about them in verse eight.

32:50.055 --> 32:56.806
It says, one day Zechariah was serving God in a temple for his order was on duty that week.

32:56.826 --> 32:59.570
As was the custom of the priests, he was chosen by Lot

32:59.650 --> 33:02.975
to enter the sanctuary of the Lord and burn incense.

33:02.995 --> 33:06.079
While the incense was being burned, a great crowd stood outside praying.

33:06.119 --> 33:11.827
While Zechariah was in the sanctuary, an angel of the Lord appeared to him.

33:12.728 --> 33:22.241
Standing to the right of the incense altar, Zechariah was shaken and overwhelmed with fear when he saw him, but the angel said, don't be afraid, Zechariah.

33:23.222 --> 33:25.746
God has heard your prayer.

33:25.766 --> 33:28.850
Your wife Elizabeth will give you a son.

33:29.186 --> 33:31.809
and you are to name Him John.

33:33.690 --> 33:37.154
God has heard your prayer.

33:39.556 --> 33:44.841
Now this prayer, this was a prayer that Zechariah and Elizabeth had put to rest.

33:46.683 --> 33:50.447
They had come to terms with the fact that it was too late for them to have a baby.

33:51.088 --> 33:54.731
And a baby is just not a part of our story.

33:55.232 --> 33:56.012
They're too old.

33:56.733 --> 33:57.554
But yet,

33:57.730 --> 34:02.015
The Bible tells us that they continued to faithfully serve God.

34:02.496 --> 34:05.620
Zechariah was just doing his duty.

34:05.720 --> 34:06.421
He was a priest.

34:06.861 --> 34:14.410
Burning incense was something that happened twice a day in the temple, but this time he got chosen to go in and burn the incense.

34:15.111 --> 34:23.922
You know, I believe that God often does the biggest work in the most ordinary parts of my life.

34:25.058 --> 34:34.210
I believe that God saw every single day that Zechariah showed up and continued his duties day after day.

34:35.491 --> 34:37.674
Zechariah was on duty.

34:38.575 --> 34:40.778
He was doing his job.

34:41.799 --> 34:53.714
And an angel comes to him and tells him that his son, the one he never thought he would have, the one he had given up on ever having his son

34:54.050 --> 34:56.360
is gonna be the forerunner of Christ.

34:57.244 --> 35:04.114
All this time, they had prayed for a child, they believed for a baby, and it never came to pass until the time was right.

35:05.154 --> 35:07.476
And God was about to place a baby in their laps.

35:07.556 --> 35:09.638
It just wasn't just any baby.

35:09.979 --> 35:11.580
This was a special baby.

35:11.860 --> 35:15.584
This was a baby that the prophets Isaiah and Malachi foretold.

35:15.844 --> 35:19.247
This was the baby that had to be born at this time.

35:19.548 --> 35:23.031
And God chose Zechariah and Elizabeth to raise this baby.

35:23.071 --> 35:24.112
You know who it was, right?

35:24.853 --> 35:29.517
John the Baptist, the one who would prepare the way for Jesus.

35:29.657 --> 35:34.482
I mean, arguably the second most important baby born in the New Testament, right?

35:34.754 --> 35:43.885
And God chose Elizabeth, but he wanted to use her pregnancy in her old age to confirm to Mary what was going to come to pass for her.

35:44.266 --> 35:46.689
The time had finally come.

35:46.709 --> 35:50.033
I thought about calling this message.

35:50.613 --> 35:52.035
He heard you the first time.

35:56.220 --> 36:00.866
Because I want you to know that God hears our prayers.

36:01.286 --> 36:04.210
God hears our prayers.

36:05.346 --> 36:07.049
God hears your prayers.

36:08.151 --> 36:14.421
And just like Pastor Stephen taught us last week, he doesn't need our prompts.

36:17.326 --> 36:24.658
God has been speaking to me so much about prayer this year, about what it is and kind of more what it's not.

36:25.058 --> 36:28.322
And there's so many beautiful aspects of prayer.

36:28.602 --> 36:29.563
There's written prayers.

36:29.603 --> 36:30.564
There's spoken prayers.

36:30.604 --> 36:31.605
There's silent prayers.

36:31.645 --> 36:32.847
There's private prayers.

36:32.907 --> 36:34.148
There's public prayers.

36:34.188 --> 36:41.817
But what I am learning is that prayer is mostly about coming into God's presence.

36:41.837 --> 36:43.118
However, you can do that.

36:43.839 --> 36:47.283
It's about bringing Him into your situation.

36:47.323 --> 36:53.970
And as God's child, as God's children, we have so many biblical examples.

36:54.210 --> 36:58.296
that tell us that we can and we should come to Him with our requests.

36:58.316 --> 37:04.345
That is perfectly acceptable and you should come to God with your requests.

37:04.365 --> 37:12.357
But I want you to know if all you ever do is make requests, you are not going to experience the power and the presence of God in your life.

37:13.539 --> 37:21.170
If God worked like Santa and you could just send them a letter every December, and magically all your hopes and dreams would come true,

37:22.178 --> 37:24.340
There would be no faith required in that.

37:24.360 --> 37:27.083
There would be no relationship needed in that.

37:27.283 --> 37:29.165
It's just some guy that you write a letter to.

37:29.205 --> 37:36.993
A couple of months ago, I was so frustrated about a situation that I've been praying about for years.

37:37.694 --> 37:42.799
I mean, I have brought this thing to God and I've asked him to change it.

37:44.280 --> 37:49.906
I have suggested many ways that I thought he could change it.

37:50.146 --> 37:56.456
I've even been so good as to work out the times that I thought that God would move in this situation.

37:56.516 --> 38:01.585
And I found myself back in that same place of frustration.

38:01.645 --> 38:11.200
And I hope it's okay for me to tell you this, but I said to God, God, I can't talk to you about this anymore.

38:13.284 --> 38:17.170
God, I don't even know what to say to you anymore.

38:18.306 --> 38:20.209
When I pray about this, nothing happens.

38:20.269 --> 38:23.273
So I'm just not going to talk about it anymore.

38:25.196 --> 38:28.540
I feel like God whispered right straight into my heart.

38:29.221 --> 38:31.865
I feel like He said to me, good.

38:36.471 --> 38:37.252
I can work with that.

38:39.535 --> 38:41.939
Just come into my presence, Holly.

38:41.959 --> 38:43.261
You don't have to talk to me about it?

38:43.761 --> 38:44.743
Just come into my presence.

38:45.283 --> 38:47.186
Just sit in my presence.

38:47.842 --> 38:49.084
I heard you the first time.

38:50.846 --> 38:56.893
Remember there's nothing wrong with being persistent and having the faith to keep praying for God to do something in your life.

38:57.153 --> 39:10.930
The Bible supports that, but sometimes you need to exercise the faith that believes that he heard you and that he's working in your situation.

39:11.106 --> 39:17.655
that believes that he is telling a story on this earth that is so much bigger than you and your situation.

39:17.675 --> 39:26.847
And faithfulness sometimes looks like showing up to the things that we know we're called to do just while we wait for the things that we hope for.

39:26.907 --> 39:29.631
That's what Zachariah was doing.

39:30.953 --> 39:33.697
There's a lady who's a part of our e-fam.

39:34.317 --> 39:37.682
And she sent this letter to Pastor Stephen

39:37.762 --> 39:41.769
And thank you, by the way, to all of the people who send us letters.

39:42.650 --> 39:44.213
Your stories mean a lot to us.

39:44.974 --> 39:51.645
And this story, I want to share this part of this story with you because it's just incredibly incredible.

39:51.686 --> 39:52.307
She writes this.

39:53.208 --> 39:59.058
I have been faithfully watching Elevation Worship Services at 9.30 a.m. Sunday mornings for the last six years.

39:59.490 --> 40:01.112
I wanted to write you for a long time.

40:01.132 --> 40:09.083
I wanted to share my testimony with you and let you know how you changed this particular chapter in my life with one of your sermons.

40:09.523 --> 40:14.049
She says, your sermons continue to bring me hope and comfort.

40:14.890 --> 40:23.922
And she goes on to talk about how she was raised in the church and her husband

40:24.002 --> 40:27.187
was raised in the church and they raised their children in church.

40:27.247 --> 40:32.995
They had three boys and one baby girl after their three boys were born.

40:33.316 --> 40:36.260
And they raised their children to believe in God.

40:36.380 --> 40:37.542
They raised them in church.

40:37.562 --> 40:38.764
They taught them to love God.

40:39.084 --> 40:47.937
And then she begins to share how in 2021, their daughter became involved with some very bad influences.

40:48.297 --> 40:51.442
And she began to make some really poor choices.

40:51.554 --> 41:03.167
And she eventually ended up, this is every mother's nightmare, she ended up living with a man who was an alcoholic and who was abusive to her daughter both mentally and physically.

41:03.307 --> 41:07.091
And she says that they prayed fervently for their daughter.

41:07.451 --> 41:20.946
And she says that finally one day their daughter came to them and she said she wanted to come home, but she said she couldn't because she believed that this man would harm her and harm her family if she left.

41:21.666 --> 41:27.993
And in the letter, she says that the situation just felt helpless and hopeless.

41:29.354 --> 41:38.725
And then she says, on July 2, 2022, we got a call that she had been involved in an accident.

41:40.026 --> 41:46.553
And she said they rushed to the scene and they saw where her car was totaled and found out that she had been drinking.

41:46.613 --> 41:51.058
And so right there, she was charged with a felony DUI.

41:51.522 --> 41:57.448
And they took her to the hospital and they treated her for bruises and a broken nose and a broken hand.

41:57.968 --> 42:07.558
And she writes this, she said, she said, I had to help her in the backseat of the police car once she was released from the ER.

42:08.479 --> 42:11.602
She was on her way to jail for the night.

42:12.303 --> 42:15.105
And initially my thoughts were, really God?

42:16.867 --> 42:19.890
We gave her to you to watch over her.

42:20.578 --> 42:23.001
And this is what you allow to happen."

42:23.862 --> 42:33.515
And then she says, yes, I believe he did because she was able to get out of that man's house safely and move back home with us.

42:34.637 --> 42:38.082
And we know that without his intervention, she would not have even survived the crash.

42:39.544 --> 42:43.609
And she came home and she spent the next several months in AA and in therapy.

42:44.210 --> 42:50.258
She was extremely faithful to her recovery and she made the necessary changes in her life and they were feeling really hopeful

42:50.434 --> 42:52.617
But her court date came around.

42:52.677 --> 43:05.893
And on February 20th, 2023, she goes on to say that to their utter devastation, their daughter was sentenced to 180 days in jail.

43:07.435 --> 43:11.400
And she goes on to write, she says, I was angry with God.

43:11.440 --> 43:19.570
I could not believe that he would allow this to happen now after she had spent so many months turning her life around

43:19.874 --> 43:20.435
Jail?

43:21.476 --> 43:24.220
She said, I spent my whole life trusting in God.

43:24.901 --> 43:28.246
And then she says, side note, trust was my word for the year.

43:29.068 --> 43:31.551
But now my trust was gone.

43:33.855 --> 43:34.876
This is where it gets good.

43:36.599 --> 43:38.882
The next Sunday, I was home alone.

43:39.563 --> 43:41.686
And out of habit, I think, LOL.

43:42.347 --> 43:43.730
I turned your service on.

43:44.651 --> 43:49.458
The songs they sang that day were all my favorites, which I didn't want to hear, but they made me cry.

43:49.762 --> 43:52.807
God was working despite my acceptance, despite my anger.

43:53.428 --> 43:58.035
The title of your sermon was, God is up to something upstream.

43:58.496 --> 43:59.597
Anybody remember that one?

44:04.044 --> 44:07.730
I kept telling myself he was up to something, but I wasn't having it.

44:08.130 --> 44:14.119
You kept giving examples in the Bible of how God was always 20 miles ahead of your situation or circumstance.

44:14.419 --> 44:15.481
He's 20 miles ahead.

44:15.761 --> 44:16.763
He's 20 miles ahead.

44:17.043 --> 44:20.428
I kept hearing it over and over again, and something hit me.

44:21.470 --> 44:27.138
I grabbed my phone and typed in directions to the county jail from my house.

44:30.343 --> 44:31.104
I'm gonna cry.

44:32.426 --> 44:33.628
Guess how far away it was?

44:33.648 --> 44:35.711
20 miles.

44:37.353 --> 44:37.874
She said,

44:39.842 --> 44:40.903
I dropped to the ground.

44:41.904 --> 44:44.046
Tears were flowing down my face.

44:46.428 --> 44:49.271
God was 20 miles ahead, she said.

44:49.311 --> 45:02.023
And a week or so later, in our conversation, she told me she was having Bible study in her cell and teaching and singing elevation music to all the girls.

45:07.288 --> 45:09.330
She did four and a half months time

45:09.858 --> 45:13.404
And the day we picked her up was one of the best days we have had.

45:13.824 --> 45:17.390
God gave us so much grace and so much mercy.

45:17.430 --> 45:19.713
During those months, I thought I would never make it through.

45:20.254 --> 45:21.075
Wasn't in her plan.

45:21.997 --> 45:24.321
She said, please keep my family and myself in your prayers.

45:25.062 --> 45:32.994
We have learned to take one day at a time and we just keep praising our Father for all he does.

45:34.977 --> 45:35.538
Amen.

45:42.210 --> 45:43.051
What a story.

45:43.111 --> 45:45.634
God is so faithful.

45:46.435 --> 45:47.476
He's so faithful.

45:48.197 --> 45:50.640
He hears us when we pray.

45:50.680 --> 45:53.623
He heard you the first time.

45:53.643 --> 45:56.927
He knows things that we don't know.

45:56.947 --> 46:06.157
And we have to trust the one who is working in our situation even when it doesn't make sense.

46:08.420 --> 46:10.162
I love how the letter ended with

46:10.306 --> 46:17.973
We just keep praising our Father one day at a time because I think that's it.

46:20.095 --> 46:29.324
Maybe if you find yourself in a place this Christmas where you're wondering if God heard your prayer or you're feeling like nothing is happening in your situation.

46:30.765 --> 46:39.794
Maybe we can take our cues from this lady who's a part of our Epham and from Mary because Mary didn't prompt

46:39.970 --> 46:40.310
God.

46:41.512 --> 46:46.399
She didn't list out all of the things that God was going to need to do to work everything out for her.

46:46.779 --> 46:48.982
She didn't remind God of all the things that could go wrong.

46:49.002 --> 46:52.968
She didn't suggest people who were more qualified for this calling.

46:54.049 --> 46:56.152
She praised her Savior.

46:57.234 --> 47:04.904
She was blessed because she believed that God believed in her, that God was going to lead her, and that God heard her prayer.

47:04.924 --> 47:09.330
She was blessed before she had seen any of these things.

47:09.506 --> 47:10.407
come to pass.

47:11.588 --> 47:14.131
And Luke tells us, he gives us her prayer.

47:14.251 --> 47:15.872
It's called the Magnificat.

47:17.013 --> 47:20.056
And she says, my soul magnifies the Lord.

47:20.337 --> 47:28.104
My heart rejoices and God my Savior, for he lifts the lowly and he has done great things for me.

47:28.124 --> 47:31.007
He hadn't even done anything for her yet when she said that.

47:31.748 --> 47:34.050
She said, he has done great things for me.

47:34.070 --> 47:38.194
I want you to know that praise is a reset.

47:39.490 --> 47:45.356
It enables you to take your eyes off of your situation and place them on your savior.

47:46.998 --> 47:49.341
So I want us to follow Mary's example today.

47:49.381 --> 47:52.664
And I want us to magnify the Lord together.

47:52.905 --> 47:59.792
I want us to bless his name for who he is and for what he's done so that we can trust him with what's next.

48:00.894 --> 48:02.635
Hey, I hope you enjoyed the podcast.

48:02.716 --> 48:04.978
And if you did, make sure to share it.

48:05.122 --> 48:09.808
and subscribe so we can get you all of these new messages as soon as they're available.

48:10.389 --> 48:13.893
I also want to take a moment and thank all of you who are a part of Elevation.

48:14.353 --> 48:23.144
Whether you support us financially or serve with us or just share these messages, it's because of you that we're able to reach people all around the world.

48:23.505 --> 48:29.212
And if you want more information on how to be a part of Elevation, click the link in the description.

48:29.733 --> 48:30.654
Thanks again for listening.

48:30.694 --> 48:34.098
Make sure to leave a review, share the message and subscribe.

48:34.306 --> 48:35.251
God bless you.

